Kim Jong Il Highly Praised  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- A lecture and book exhibition were held by the Indian Youth Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Il Sung and a lecture was given by the Tanzanian National Coordinating Committee of the Juche Idea Study Groups on May 25 and 29 on the occasion of the 43rd anniversary of Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venue of the book exhibition were famous works of the leader and books introducing the advantages of the socialist system in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lecturers noted that Kim Jong Il developed and enriched the revolutionary idea of President Kim Il Sung as required by the development of the era and revolution, thus formulating it as an integral system of the idea, theory and method of Juche, and achieved the unity and cohesion of the Party ranks and built it into a mighty party having a solid mass foundation.

Repeal of NSL Urged in South Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- Persons of culture and arts in south Korea held a "candlelight cultural event for the release of Ri Si U, a peace-loving photographer and writer, and the repeal of the National Security Law (NSL)" in Seoul on June 1, according to the south Korean Internet newspaper Thongil News. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers in the event declared they could no longer remain on-lookers to the patriotic figures falling victim to the evil law for having conducted just activities for the peace and reunification of this land, calling upon the people to turn out in the struggle for the repeal of the NSL. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed the need for all the people to pool their efforts and wage dynamic actions for the release of the patriotic figures.

Revolutionary Site Attracts Endless Stream of Visitors 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The Chosan Revolutionary Site in Jagang Province is associated with the immortal exploits performed by indomitable revolutionary fighter Kim Hyong Jik. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyong Jik went to Chosan in November of Juche 7 (1918) and visited it several times later to restore the organizations of the Korean National Association (KNA) which had either been destroyed or daunted due to the Japanese imperialists' suppression and conduct dynamic activities for making a switchover in the anti-Japanese national liberation struggle in Korea. The historic buildings and relics are preserved in their original state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At Paesin School, "Sipja Uiwon" (red cross hospital) and the Chosan Agency for Public Utility he educated people and roused them to the anti-Japanese struggle, calling on the Korean nation to unite in single mind and fight against the Japs to achieve the country's independence and build a new society of workers and peasants free from exploitation and oppression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Preserved in the meeting place on Mt. Paekho are historic relics telling how he informed members of the Korean National Association of the policy set forth at the Chongsudong Meeting and led anti-Japanese independence movement organizations in the areas along the River Amnok to turn out in the patriotic struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodonggol House is the place where he specified the tasks to be implemented by the participants in the independence movement in Chosan area in the middle of August in Juche 9 (1920) in order to carry out the policy advanced at the Kuandian Meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 600,000 people have visited the Chosan Revolutionary Site over the past more than three decades.

70th Anniversary of Victory in Pochonbo Battle Celebrated across Country  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The 70th anniversary of the victory in the historic Pochonbo battle was significantly celebrated across the country on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Art performances were given at theatres in Pyongyang and local areas to observe the day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A music and dance performance was staged by the Mansudae Art Troupe at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its repertoire included colorful numbers such as mixed duet and chorus "Song Devoted to Marshal Kim Il Sung," male vocal solo "Pochonbo, Land of Glory," serial songs "Arirang that Resounded through Jiansanfeng" and dance "Azalea in Motherland." The artistes sang in high praises of the immortal exploits of the peerlessly great man who gave origin to Songun with arms and created the ever-victorious history of the Juche-oriented revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dancing parties of youth and students took place in Pyongyang, Phyongsong, Sinuiju, Haeju, Sariwon, Wonsan, Hamhung and other places, adding to the festive atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, campfires were set up in Pyongyang, Huichon City and Manpho City and Kilju, Kyongsong, Unpha and Jangyon counties and other cities and counties to lighten the nocturnal skies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Working people and youth and students explained the contents of the reminiscences of President Kim Il Sung "With the Century," recited poems and made speeches around campfires.

Torchlight Procession and Bonfire Gathering on Pochonbo Battle Anniversary 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pochon, June 4 (KCNA) -- A torchlight procession and a bonfire gathering were held by youths and students in Pochonbo on Monday to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the victory in the historic Pochonbo battle commanded by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When darkness fell youths and students presented the letter "70th Anniversary" with torchlight on the road leading to the education ground in front of the statue of President Kim Il Sung standing high on a bank of the River Karim. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The grand torchlight procession began amid the loud playing of "The Guerilla March".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The columns of procession led by flags bearing a portrait of President Kim Il Sung and a portrait of Kim Jong Il marched past in fine array the major battle sites where members of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army poured a fire of revenge on the Japanese imperialists' ruling tools including the police substation and the sub-county office. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While the columns of the procession were marching through the street, fireworks fizzled into the sky near the commanding post where President Kim Il Sung led the Pochonbo battle to victory on the historic day (June 4, 1937). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The youths and students depicted the letters "Kim Il Sung" and "Kim Jong Il" and a red flag and a torchlight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the procession was passing before the statue of President    Kim Il Sung, there burst forth loud calls including "Long live the revolutionary idea of the great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung!", "Let us defend the revolutionary headquarters headed by the great Comrade Kim Jong Il with our lives!" and "Let us youths carry the revolutionary cause of Juche to accomplishment following the Songun leadership of the great leader Comrade Kim Jong Il!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The procession meandered to the site of the bonfire gathering. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, in his speech urged all the youths and students to deeply cherish the undying Songun feats of President Kim Il Sung in their hearts and perform their mission and duty as the reserve combat unit and shock brigade of the supreme commander in upholding the cause of the Workers' Party of Korea, following the sturdy spirit of devotedly defending the leader and ardent patriotism displayed by the anti-Japanese revolutionary forerunners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the gathering the part depicting the Pochonbo battle from the long epic "Mt. Paektu" was recited and speeches were made.

U.S. Ambition for Preemptive Attack Assailed  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- As already reported, the United States is actively promoting three-country cooperation by involving Australia in its joint study into the establishment of the Missile Defense System (MD) with Japan. In another development, it is increasing the combat capability of its forces while reinforcing its special troops in south Korea, Japan and other parts of the Asia-Pacific region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today says that such movements as the joint development of MD and the forward deployment of task forces are a revelation of the U.S. hegemonic and strong-arm policy to hold an upper-hand of strength in the Asia-Pacific region and the rest of the world and contain its strategic enemies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are prompted by its strategic scheme to realize its ambition for preemptive attack based on an unchallenged upper-hand of strength, the paper notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The establishment of security posture touted by the U.S. is aimed to bolster armed forces and hold military supremacy in a bid to attain upper-hand of strength worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lurking behind the U.S. theory of "upper-hand of strength" is its attempt to mount a preemptive attack. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Peace and security have been wrecked and the danger of war increased in different regions of the world by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many countries of the world are now directing big efforts into increasing their military capability for self-defense, remaining highly vigilant against the U.S. arms buildup and military policy of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such developments are seriously affecting the global peace and the development of international situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With nothing can the U.S. cover up its criminal nature as a wrecker of peace and security and a mastermind of escalating the tension.

World Environment Day Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- Papers here Tuesday dedicate articles to the World Environment Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says in a signed article that diverse activities and functions are now under way in the DPRK according to the theme for this year designated by the United Nations Environment Programme. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has long paid great attention to the environmental protection helpful to promoting the people's health, increasing the scenic beauty of cities and providing better living conditions and environment. Thanks to the correct environmental protection policy of the DPRK government, the DPRK is recognized by the world community as a country with good environment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The issue of environmental protection is now presenting itself as a very important and urgent one worldwide. Ecological environment is being seriously contaminated in various parts of the world for various reasons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No country can be an exception in the work to protect the environment on the earth. Good results can be expected in this work only when all countries make positive efforts, aware of the urgency and importance of the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will conduct positive work for environmental protection, maintaining close touch with international organizations in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson in a signed article notes that global warming is the most serious worldwide problem at present, adding that the melting of ice in the polar areas is the most vivid example of it. In order to cope with the situation the DPRK is taking steps to increase and firmly protect fresh water resources, stop soil from being washed away and prevent damage by strong winds and floods.

Japan Urged to Settle Its Crime-woven Past 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The recent 8th Asian solidarity meeting for solution to the issue of "comfort women" for imperial Japanese army in a joint statement strongly demanded the Japanese government open to the public all the reports and data related to the past crimes committed by it in Korea and other Asian countries and take prompt political and legal measures to fulfill legal responsibilities including making a formal apology and compensation for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Timed to coincide with this, the UN Committee against Torture urged the Japanese government to educate the people in the cause of discriminative actions including sexual abuses and relieve victims. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson today in a signed commentary carried in this regard accuses Japan of refusing to honestly admit its past criminal acts and persistently evading the responsibility for making apology and compensation for them, defying the above-said demand of the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries seek an ulterior aim in justifying their past crimes and refusing to apologize and compensate for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is a revelation of their invariable ambition to reinvade Asia, come what may. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that there is no future for Japan as long as it is keen to repeat its past history of aggression, far from drawing a proper lesson from its crime-woven past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' acts of tampering with Japan's history and challenging the demand of the international community for admitting its past crimes and apologizing for them would only lead them to self-destruction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries would be well advised to earnestly opt for redressing Japan's past, well aware of the demand of the present era.

Angolan Military Delegation Leaves
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The military delegation of Angola led by Minister of Defense Kundi Paihama flew back Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During its stay in the DPRK the delegation visited Mangyongdae, the birthplace of President Kim Il Sung.

DPRK Strives to Prevent Global Warming
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The abnormal climate phenomena caused by global warming has been raised today as a hard problem in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The UN Environment Programme set "Global Warming" as the theme for this year on the occasion of the World Environment Day (June 5), since it threatens the life and security of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Organized on the occasion of the day in the country were colorful events including a scientific symposium and a national seminar on reducing the emission of atmospheric green-house gases and preventing global warming, and film shows for arousing profound social interest in the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jong Hyong Il, a department director in the Ministry of Land and Environment Preservation, told KCNA that the DPRK which has been suffering from the upward temperature in recent years is conducting varied activities in accordance with the world trend for preventing such phenomena. He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It deepens the scientific researches into elevation of energy efficiency and utilization of regenerated energy and directs efforts to the work for applying the results. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The construction of large and minor hydro-power stations is being pushed ahead through an all-people movement and application of wind power positively encouraged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An effort to improve the efficiency of solar batteries is being made, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a brisk tree-planting campaign is being launched to increase the adsorption of carbon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, a signatory to the Kyoto Protocol and the Montreal Protocol on Substances Destroying Ozone Layer, is doing its best to restrict and reduce the emission of atmospheric green-house gases as much as possible.

New Stamp Issued
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- A new stamp has been issued in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in commemoration of the 70th anniversary of the victory in the Pochonbo battle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The battle was a storm mounted by the main unit of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army under the command of President Kim Il Sung in the township of Pochon, Pochon County, Ryanggang Province on June 4, Juche 26 (1937). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The victory in the Pochonbo battle inspired the Korean people with the firm confidence that the Koreans are not dead but alive and will certainly win victory if they fight against Japanese imperialism and powerfully aroused them in the struggle against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also it dealt a heavy military and political blow to the Japanese imperialist aggressors and shook their colonial rule over Korea to the very foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen in the stamp is the oil painting "Torchlight of Pochonbo" under the letters "Commemoration of the 70th anniversary of the victory in the Pochonbo battle" in the upper part. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The painting shows President Kim Il Sung making a speech calling for the anti-Japanese struggle before people at the end of the battle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The face value of the stamp is 120 won.

Immortal Exploits in Keeping Life-line of Revolution
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The traditions of Paektu, life-line of the revolution, are being carried forward with credit in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new era for inheriting the revolutionary traditions was opened up in the middle of the 1950s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il made an expedition to the revolutionary battle sites in the area of Mt.  Paektu, leading an expedition party formed with students of the then Pyongyang Middle School No.1 in June Juche 45 (1956) when the enemies within and without made desperate efforts to obliterate the revolutionary traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic expedition was a stern declaration that there were no other traditions but the revolutionary traditions of Paektu established by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He published many famous works including "Let us cultivate the revolutionary spirit of Paektu among the rising generation" and "Let us brilliantly carry forward the revolutionary traditions of Juche" while leading the Korean revolution.  He, in the works, gave a comprehensive exposition of the theoretical and practical problems arising in inheriting the revolutionary traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, thus, provided such the fundamental guidelines for accomplishing the revolutionary cause as the idea that the attitude toward the revolutionary traditions is directly related with the stand and viewpoint on the leader and the idea and theory on embodying the revolutionary traditions in socialist construction and in all fabrics of social life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He saw to it that all the ideas, theories and policies of the Workers' Party of Korea were shaped to defend and glorify the revolutionary ideas and exploits of the leader and created a shining example in building the sacred temple of the revolution and the grand palace for the education in the revolutionary traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his leadership, the Monument to the Victorious Battle in Pochonbo, Samjiyon Grand Monument, Monument to the Victorious Battle of the Musan Area and Phophyong Monument to Revolutionary Activities were erected as immortal grand edifices and the revolutionary battle and historic sites have been converted into centers for the education in the revolutionary traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His on-the-spot guidance to the revolutionary battle sites in the Mt. Paektu area in March 2000 marked a turning-point in sprucing up the area as a sacred place of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il gave instructions that the glorious revolutionary traditions of the WPK should be glorified for all ages, while giving on-the-spot guidance to the field of the preservation of revolutionary sites in Kanggye City recently.

Agreement Signed between DPRK and China
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- An agreement of the 46th meeting of the Cooperation Committee of the Korea-China Border River Navigation, was inked here on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were members of delegations of the Korean and Chinese sides to the committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was signed by Ri Nam Jong, head of the delegation of the Korean side, and Zhang Yong, head of the delegation of the Chinese side.

High Tribute to Kim Hyong Jik Paid
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the statue of Kim Hyong Jik, an indomitable revolutionary fighter and outstanding leader of the anti-Japanese national liberation movement in Korea, in Ponghwa-ri, Kangdong County and his grave in Mangyongdae on June 5 on the occasion of the 81st anniversary of his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen before the statue and grave were wreaths from General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at wreath-laying ceremonies were Kim Yong Nam, Kim Il Chol, Choe Thae Bok, Kim Ki Nam, Choe Yong Rim, Chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party Kim Yong Dae, officials of party and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and servicepersons, working people and school youth and children in the city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Laid before the statue and grave were wreaths in the name of the WPK Central Committee, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also placed were wreaths in the name of ministries, national institutions, working people's organizations, military academies, educational and media organs, and party and power organs, factories, farms and schools in the city as well as bouquets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid a silent tribute to Kim Hyong Jik with humble reverence for him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, wreaths and bouquets were laid before his statues standing at Kim Hyong Jik Military Medical University and in Sakju and Junggang counties on the same day.

DPRK Delegation Back from Nigeria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- The delegation of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea led by Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, returned home on Tuesday after visiting Nigeria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was met at the airport by Choe Yong Rim, secretary general of the SPA Presidium, and officials concerned and Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Liu Xiaoming and Paschal Ibe, Nigerian charge d'affaires a.i. here.

Choe Thae Bok Meets Outgoing Cuban Ambassador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, met and had a conversation with Cuban Ambassador to the DPRK Ruben Perez Valdes when the latter paid a farewell call on him Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Kim Thae Jong, vice director of a department of the WPK Central Committee, and a staff member of the Cuban embassy here.

World Environment Day Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- An event took place at Changdok School on June 5 to observe World Environment Day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials in the field of environmental protection and teachers, employees and students of the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present on invitation were the associate director of the "Environmental Education Media Project" whose office is located in China and environment experts of different countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guests laid bouquets before the statue of President Kim Il Sung at the school and paid a tribute to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After going round the historic building where the President studied, they were briefed on the history of the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The function heard speeches on the importance of the environment protection. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants watched a recorded material on global warming and pictures on the theme of it before appreciating a performance given by an art group of the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guests appreciated the schoolchildren's activities of the care-for-the-homeland team.

Visits
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- A delegation of officials of the Workers' Party of Korea headed by Secretary of the Pyongyang City Committee of the WPK Kim Jin Ha left here Tuesday to visit China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A friendship delegation of the Communist Party of China led by Secretary of the Gansu Provincial Committee of the CPC Lu Hao arrived here on the same day.

Rodong Sinmun critica doctrina de "superioridad de fuerzas" de EE.UU.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 5 de junio (ATCC) -- Como ya trascendidos, Estados Unidos impulsa la investigacion conjunta para implantar el Sistema Antimisiles en colaboracion trilateral con Japon y Australia. Por otra parte, incrementa la combatividad de sus efectivos en la region de Asia-Pacifico, inclusive el Sur de Corea y Japon, al emplazar adicionalmente ahi a las tropas especiales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al respecto, el diario Rodong Sinmun difundio este martes un comentario individual que senala en particular: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El desarrollo conjunto del Sistema Antimisiles, el emplazamiento en las zonas avanzadas de las fuerzas moviles para el ataque y otras maniobras del imperio parten de su politica hegemonica y despotica de resistir a los "rivales estrategicos" al tomar la "superioridad de las fuerzas" en el ambito mundial, en particular, en la region de Asia y el Pacifico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A la larga, ese intento estrategico consiste en satisfacer su ambicion de atacar preventivamente a otros paises aprovechando la absoluta "superioridad de las fuerzas".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por tal razon, el "establecimiento de la disposicion para la seguridad", de que habla tanto EE.UU., es en su esencia el lema de aumento armamentista y de hegemonia militar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Hoy dia, por culpa del imperio, se quiebran la paz y la seguridad en varias regiones del mundo y se acrecienta el peligro de guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Muy alertos ante el aumento armamentista y la agresiva politica militar de EE.UU., numerosos paises del orbe prestan mucha atencion al fortalecimiento de sus fuerzas armadas para la autodefensa. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Estas circunstancias tienen graves consecuencias en la preservacion de la paz mundial y el desenvolvimiento de la situacion internacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  EE.UU. nunca podra ocultar su identidad criminal como perturbador de la paz y la seguridad y responsable de exacerbacion de la tension.

Minju Joson denuncia a Japon que no quiere recompensar
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 5 de junio (ATCC) -- La Declaracion Conjunta aprobada en la recien efectuada VIII Reunion Solidaria de Asia para la solucion del problema de las "ex consoladoras sexuales" del viejo ejercito japones demando fuertemente que el gobierno de este pais isleno publique todos los informes y datos relacionados con los crimenes cometidos en el siglo pasado en Corea y otros paises asiaticos y tome pronto las medidas politicas y legales para cumplir su responsabilidad juridica por el respecto, inclusive pedir perdon oficialmente y recompensar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Coincidiendo con esto, el Comite de la ONU contra Torturas demando al gobierno japones la educacion sobre la causa de actos de discriminacion como la violacion sexual y el auxilio a sus victimas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En un comentario individual de este martes el periodico Minju Joson senala que al desoir tal demanda de la sociedad internacional, Japon no reconoce sinceramente sus actos criminales del pasado y evade a toda costa su responsabilidad de disculparse e indemnizar y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La intencion de los reaccionarios islenos, que justifican porfiadamente las fechorias del pasado, parte de su invariable ambicion de retomar el camino de agresion a Asia cueste lo que cueste. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta claro que no hay futuro para Japon que en vez de sacar lecciones del pasado criminal actua freneticamente para reproducir la historia de agresion del siglo anterior. Si los reaccionarios japoneses desafian a la demanda de la sociedad internacional recurriendo a la tergiversacion de la historia, adelantaran solo su bancarrota. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ellos deben ver correctamente la demanda de la epoca y expiar sus barbaridades del pasado.

Festividades de la juventud por triunfo en batalla de Pochombo 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pochon, 4 de junio (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar el dia 4 en esta localidad la marcha con antorcha y el encuentro al lado de hoguera de los jovenes y estudiantes en conmemoracion del 70o aniversario del triunfo en la historica batalla de Pochombo, comandada el 4 de junio del 26 (1937) de la Era Juche por el Presidente Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al anochecer, los reunidos inscribieron con antorchas en sus manos las letras de "Aniversario 70" en la carretera contigua a la explanada frente a la estatua de bronce del Presidente, erguida a las orillas del rio Karim. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El acto comenzo mientras resonaba la cancion "Marcha militar de la guerrilla". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Siguiendo las banderas con efigies del Presidente Kim Il Sung y del Dirigente Kim Jong Il, las filas desfilaron a pasos firmes por delante del puesto de policia, el ayuntamiento cantonal y otros organismos gubernamentales de los imperialistas japoneses de aquel entonces, agujereados por las metrallas de venganza de los asaltantes del Ejercito Revolucionario Popular de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Cuando los marchantes se desbordaron a las avenidas adyacentes, se tiraron salvas sucesivas en las cercanias del puesto de mando donde el Presidente dirigio la batalla de Pochombo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Los participantes describieron con sus antorchas las letras "Kim Il Sung" y "Kim Jong Il" y las maquetas de la bandera roja y antorcha. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mientras pasaban por la estatua de bronce del Presidente, las columnas corearon fuertemente las consignas de "!Viva la idea revolucionaria del gran Lider, camarada Kim Il Sung!", "!Defendamos a costa de la vida a la Direccion de la Revolucion encabezada por el gran camarada Kim Jong Il!", "!Que los jovenes lleven a feliz termino la causa revolucionaria del Juche siguiendo la guia del Songun del gran Dirigente, camarada Kim Jong Il!", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Las columnas se dirigieron al lugar habilitado para el acto al pie de la hoguera. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Kim Kyong Ho, primer secretario del Comite Central de la Union de la Juventud Socialista Kim Il Sung, apunto en su discurso que todos los jovenes y estudiantes deben asimilar las inmortales proezas del Songun del Presidente y aprender el espiritu de defensa a ultranza al lider y el gran patriotismo, manifestados por los martires revolucionarios antijaponeses, para cumplir satisfactoriamente con su mision y deber del destacamento de reserva y de la brigada del Comandante Supremo en apoyar la causa del Partido del Trabajo de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion fue recitada la parte relativa al combate referido de la epopeya larga "Paektusan" y hubo discursos.
